snippet.title: [Swap Jam #4: Key Game: What's in the-] Last Call Playthrough (No Commentary || Both Endings)
snippet.description:
Game link: https://deepseahorror.itch.io/last-call
Commentary Version: https://youtu.be/VgyktGtldoM

Timestamp:
0:00 - intro plot and warning
0:06 - clearer intro
0:10 - gameplay

Last Call, is a short RPG Maker horror game (lighter/tamer than usual one), made by Monty/Deepseahorror, where it's a story about two men meeting at the bar who played hide and seek with a little girl. This is part of the series of games they are working with: Miscellaneous Tales from the Pale Moon City. Playthrough contains both endings, with first one being early.

Overall, I like this game. I like the two dudes' characterizations I guess for a game jam. It does provide enough to make me interested of any of them getting involved in the future games later on that they should ki- jk. Love the graphics as well, especially the fullscreen cgs/arts, it's so very cute. Overall, very nice. and makes me want to check their other games, that went under the radar. (maybe a fanart of the two, but who knows.) And about the little girl, and especially in the dev room, yeah it's understandable, still I think it also provided enough for the game jam. Overall, a good game.

Anyway, I hope you enjoy!
